summary: SummaryShape, Cover and Contour with L'Oréal Infallible Full Wear Waterproof Concealer. Waterproof, matte finish concealer that lasts up to 24 hours.
details: DetailsFeaturesMore than concealer, Full coverage matte finish for up to 24 hours - L'Oréal's extra large applicator provides full coverage in just one stroke for a flawless matte finish that lasts all dayThe waterproof formula won't transfer, fade, or crease, so your full coverage look is locked in all day - The creamy texture is non-greasy and easy to apply - a little goes along wayChoose a shade that best matches your skin tone to conceal imperfections, Go 1-2 shades deeper to contour and 1-2 shade lighter to highlight and brightenThis full coverage formula completely covers imperfections, minimizes redness and scars - It can also be used on the body to minimize the appearance of stretch marks, veins, and bruisesL'Oréal Paris Infallible Full Wear Concealer in multiple full coverage shades for every skin toneItem 2538176How To UseApply concealer directly on to imperfections and blend with finger, a brush or blender. Pro Tip: To best conceal dark circles, apply in a triangle under each eye and blend.IngredientsWater, Undecane, Glycerin, Dimethicone, Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Pentylene Glycol, Butylene Glycol, Tridecane, Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone, Hexyl Laurate, Magnesium Sulfate, Polyhydroxystearic Acid, Octyldodecanol, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Cellulose Gum, Ethylhexylglycerin, Silica Silylate, Acrylonitrile/Methyl Methacrylate/Vinylidene Chloride Copolymer, Parfum / Fragrance, Trihydroxystearin, Aluminum Hydroxide, Acetylated Glycol Stearate, Isobutane, Hexyl Cinnamal, Benzyl Salicylate, Linalool, Alpha-Isomethyl Ionone, Benzyl Alcohol, Tocopherol, Citronellol, Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil / Sunflower Seed Oil, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate. May Contain: CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, CI 77510 / Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide.
how_to_use: Apply concealer directly on to imperfections and blend with finger, a brush or blender. Pro Tip: To best conceal dark circles, apply in a triangle under each eye and blend.
ingredients: Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil / Sunflower Seed Oil

reviews.headline: I have purchased this concealer several times.
reviews.comments: I love the coverage and applicator. Makes a great primer for eye shadow.

reviews.headline: Would not recommend for mature, dry, fine lined skin.
reviews.comments: Very thick formula. Waterproof makes it dry quickly but too dry for my fine lines. It stated no creasing, but it did. Not the right product for me.

reviews.headline: Good in a pinch
reviews.comments: My go to when i run out of Tarte shape tape. Very similar, but not quite as good. Working in the heat and sweating makes it look a little cakey and seperates. Other than that it's not bad. Makes a good cheap substitute.

reviews.headline: Not good for textured skin
reviews.comments: I really wanted to like this product, it's pigmented and lightweight. A little goes a long way, and the shade match was one of the best I've found. Unfortunately, it clings to dry patches and emphasizes texture. If textured skin isnt an issue for you, you might like this, but it's a no for me

reviews.headline: Buying This again!
reviews.comments: I love this concealer not only is it waterproof but makes my undereyes look flawless

reviews.headline: not the best concealer
reviews.comments: cakey and creases bad under the eyes. has a weird smell

reviews.headline: Super drying
reviews.comments: Tried on separate occasions, thought first time my undereyes were just not hydrated enough as I had applied my cream about a half hour prior, tried again but about 15 minutes elapsed since i put eye cream on, got the same, DRYYYY under eye and it just started to flake off. :(

reviews.headline: shocked!!!
reviews.comments: I never care to leave reviews on anything but I had to share that I have so many concealers that all are dry, crease easily, and remove from the outer corner of my watery eyes. It was also a combo with the infallible blurring powder but my undereyes were perfect and brightening all day!! I also did a couple small dots of the concealer + blended with my finger which surprisingly worked so well. I was expecting to return this like the other concealers ive tried, but I love it!

reviews.headline: the worst concealer i've ever used
reviews.comments: I have used this product multiple times, for different kinds of looks. I have tried using primer, not using primer, applying a small amount and nothing works. This concealer is EXTREMELY drying even if you apply moisturizer heavily. It flakes and cakes so much. I have never seen a concealer that flakes so much, it also doesnt work with any setting spray. Upon using the setting spray- it becomes ultimately patchy and starts peeling. (It does this even without spray within an hour of wear) I have given this concealer a generous amount of attempts and it has failed every time no matter the application process. I end up leaving the house looking like an absolute CLOWN. Don't waste your money on this product. Drying, cakey, flakes. The only good part about this is the amount of product you get in the bottle.

reviews.headline: Infallible indeed
reviews.comments: I'm new at using something on my face and have received nothing but compliments since I've started using this concealer.

reviews.headline: L'Oréal concealer
reviews.comments: Best drug store concealer on the market it has buildable coverage and covers dark circles and blends amazing

reviews.headline: SO GOOD
reviews.comments: i love it very great coverage and doesnt look cakey and i have acne skin and it didnt break me out!

reviews.headline: fav concealer
reviews.comments: SO good!! full coverage and blends very well. I love it < 3 < 3 < 3

reviews.headline: Too heavy
reviews.comments: This concealer looks soooo cakey its so bad. Although it covers imperfections well, it sits so heavy on the skin it's obvious that youre wearing a full coverage concealer. Also this transfers so bad, ever when set with a setting powder. If you were to lay on a pillow or hug someone, it would transfer over.

reviews.headline: eh
reviews.comments: its okay it did crease under my eye and it doesnt wear that good it wears off so that is disappointing.

reviews.headline: So Good!!
reviews.comments: This concealer has great color matches and undertones for the drugstore. This is the only concealer where I get good undertones and great coverage for an affordable price. This performs like a high end concealer imo. My fave right now! I used to like and use ELF Hydrating Camo Concealer, but I feel like they changed something with the colors and undertones, so I switched to this one. My skin tone color is 415 Honey, and my highlight color would be 410 Almond I'm guessing. I'm gonna get Almond in my next order.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: I love this concealer. It is so smooth and it brightens up under my eyes perfectly, aswell as covering red/irritated areas of my skin.

reviews.headline: My new go to!
reviews.comments: I used maybelline fit me concealer for years before i tried this! Just repurchased another tube! I saw where some were mentioning acne..which i am very prone to but i only use it under the eyes!!!

reviews.headline: Great Coverage but Breaks me out
reviews.comments: This product has Great coverage and longevity on oily skin like mine but it breaks me out. Ethylexyl palmitate and Octyldonedacol are ingredients that shouldn't be in any complexion products imho.

reviews.headline: Heavy concealer
reviews.comments: This concealer reminds me of the shape tape and I'm not a fan, I need to returned it

faceoff_positive.comments:
As I start I have oily acne prone skin with blemishes that require a full coverage foundation especially on my cheeks I am not a fan of layering my makeup just to cover them up. I want full coverage with less steps this what L'OREAL Infallible Full Wear Concealer in 420 Cocoa Waterproof.

The formula is thick but buildable I suggest using a beauty blender sponge and a flat foundation brush. I made a slight mistake by going in too heavy on my first application a I learned from that. The mistake was easily fixed by spraying my beauty blender with setting spray and blending outward.

This is a full coverage concealer so be mindful when applying. The formula while thick was easy to blend and apply it did not add any extra time to the makeup application process I do love the end look my acne scars are well hidden I do love that the wand has a thick soft bristled brush that has sufficient product on it so no wastage. Product is well controlled no drip stays put. Its also waterproof so when I sweat I don't have to worry about my makeup running or transferring
faceoff_positive.headline: Multi Tasking Foundation

faceoff_negative.comments: The thing I really like about L'Oreal is the clear labeling of cool, warm, and neutral on their cosmetic products.  I can't find this product in my local stores, and can't tell online which shades are suitable for my cool-toned skin.  Please please fix this!
faceoff_negative.headline: Missing the cool, warm, neutral identifiers!
